Linux commands
#ls : list file directory in current directory
#cd: it is a change directory funtion that works
#pwd: print working directory ; displays the current directory a user is currently working on
#mkdir: these funtion is used to create new directory
#rmdir: remove and empty directory
#rm: these function deletes files and directories
#rm -r: these function deletes directories recursively
#rm -f: these function is forced to delete without any approval or notice of confirmation
#cp: copy file directories
#mv: move file directories/it is also used to rename files directories
#cat: displays content of the a file
#touch: is to create a new file
#nano: it opens a file in the nano text editor for editing
#chmod: it changes the permission of a file or directory which makes the file or directory readable
# 
